divs: sighting detailsfrom 7am to 7:45am this morning (8\10\09) there were unusual lights over connor pass, co. kerry ireland. from our bedroom window, myself and my husband witnessed this. it appeared to be a triangular shaped craft, hovering over the lake area perhaps. we saw this from the dingle side of connor pass. the crafted shifted east and west several times and then ascended into cloud cover. the photo was taken with a small digital camera, no zoom. but if you zoom in you can see a small orb like object just over the top of the mountain. with the naked eye this object was much brighter than it appears in the photo. viewing with binoculars, we could clearly make out a triangle shape. i rang shannon air traffic control and they didn't know of any craft in the area at that hour nor was there any mountain rescue helicopters out then. i don't know what it was, but it wasn't a weather balloon, a plane, a star, a helicopter, or a ball of gas, through the binoculars there were many lights outlining a triangle shape. there was also a higher dimmer light, that might have been a star. or, it could have been another craft higher up, but it was stationary. both disappeared behind cloud cover as the morning brightened. about the time the morning flights from america to shannon airport pass over, the craft was gone. we have never seen anything like this in our lives. we are in our 50s.
Summary: Triangle shaped caft hovering over mountain for about 45 min. in the early morning
trends: There have been no other sightings in Dingle
This sighting has never been favorited.
